<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-8627] FS deleteOnExit may delete the wrong path</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8627</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;FilterFileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; is incorrectly delegating &lt;tt&gt;deleteOnExit&lt;/tt&gt; to the raw underlying fs.  This is wrong, because each fs instance is intended to maintain its own pool of temp files.  Worse yet, this means registering a file via &lt;tt&gt;ChRootedFileSystem#deleteOnExit&lt;/tt&gt; will delete the file w/o the chroot path prepended!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12600513">HADOOP-8627</key>
            <summary>FS deleteOnExit may delete the wrong path</summary>
